Senate Resolution 237
By: Senators Hickman of the 4th, Kennedy of the 18th, Gooch of the 51st, Anavitarte of the
31st and Payne of the 54th
A RESOLUTION
1 Urging the Professional Standards Commission, in collaboration with the Department of
2 Education, the Department of Early Care and Learning, the Office of Student Achievement,
3 the University System of Georgia, the Technical College System of Georgia, and the Georgia
4 Student Finance Commission, to provide recommendations to support the state's K-12
5 education workforce and teacher and school leader pipeline; and for other purposes.
6 WHEREAS, the strength and success of the state's education system is essential to the
7 economic, social, and cultural development of the state; and
8 WHEREAS, the recruitment, retention, and professional development of highly qualified
9 educators are critical to ensure that all students receive a high quality education; and
10 WHEREAS, the state is experiencing challenges in addressing teacher shortages and
11 retaining experienced educators in the early childhood and K-12 education workforce; and
12 WHEREAS, data show a strong correlation between comprehensive preparation in teacher
13 education programs and higher teacher retention rates, underscoring the importance of
14 effective educator preparation programs; and
