38 (C) Exploring partnerships with postsecondary educational institutions and other
39 stakeholders to support improvements to teacher education programs and make
40 recommendations as to the effectiveness and amount of funding to compensate student
41 teachers and the need to reinstate HOPE access to support the teacher workforce;
42 (D) Improving public awareness of the benefits, including the Teacher Retirement
43 System, and rewards of the teaching profession to attract a diverse and talented pool of
44 candidates; and
45 (E) Focusing on teacher and school leader retention strategies, including building and
46 expanding mentorship programs for new teachers and improving school leader
47 professional development and other factors that contribute to teacher turnover;
48 (3) In making such recommendations, particular emphasis should be placed on data
49 evaluation and evidence based practices that improve all aspects of the teacher and school
50 leader workforce; and
51 (4) The Professional Standards Commission should submit such recommendations to the
52 Governor according to a time frame determined by the Office of Planning and Budget, and
53 to the Senate no later than December 1, along with any proposed legislation, policy, or
54 budget changes needed to implement their recommendations.
55 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
56 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to representatives of
57 the Professional Standards Commission, the Department of Education, the Department of
58 Early Care and Learning, the Office of Student Achievement, the University System of
59 Georgia, the Technical College System of Georgia, the Georgia Student Finance
60 Commission, and the Office of Planning and Budget.
